## <a id='quota-dev'></a> Viewing Quotas

The PKS API quotas command reports your resource utilization quota as JSON.

1. To view your resource quota, run the following command:

    ```
    curl -k -H "Authorization: Bearer USER-TOKEN" https://localhost:9021/HOSTNAME/quotas/USER-ID
    ```

    Where:
    * `USER-TOKEN` is your authentication token.
    * `HOSTNAME` is your API Hostname.
    * `USER-ID` is your user account id.

## <a id='usage-dev'></a> Viewing Usage

The PKS API usages command reports your resource utilization usage as JSON.

1. To view your current allocated resource utilization, run the following command:

    ```
    curl -k -H "Authorization: Bearer USER-TOKEN" https://localhost:9021/HOSTNAME/usages/USER-ID
    ```

    Where:
    * `USER-TOKEN` is your authentication token.
    * `HOSTNAME` is your API Hostname.
    * `USER-ID` is your user account id.
